article.headline: Texas Southern 76, Angelo St. 57
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Jacques Jones scored 17 points to help lead Texas Southern to a 76-57 win over Angelo State on Thursday night. Texas Southern (4-7) jumped ahead 10-2 in the first four minutes and held the lead throughout. The Tigers took a 41-31 lead into halftime. Jones' 7-for-11 field goal shooting made him the only Texas Southern player to score in double figures. Chris Moore led the Tigers with eight rebounds. Marcus Hubbard led Angelo State (4-7) with 14 points and seven rebounds. He hit all four of his free throw attempts. Turner Phipps added 12 points, including 2-for-3 3-pointers. Ontario McKee had 11 and Roger Johnson had 10. Texas Southern shot 50 percent for the game to 42 percent for Angelo State. Texas Southern won the rebounding contest, 33-26.
